body:
The official name for Markdown on GitHub is GitHub Flavored Markdown, which is a self- explanatory extension of the default Markdown.

This time we will apply the GitHub css of highlight.js to convert Markdown text to HTML.

[GitHub Flavored Markdown spec](https://github.github.com/gfm/)

Libraries used in this project

-  [highlight.js](https://highlightjs.org/)
-  [marked.js](https://github.com/markedjs/marked)


### Introduction

```bash
$ npm i highlight.js marked
```
If you want to run the tips code, you must also install `crypto- es` at the same time.

#### Convert GFM to HTML

Convert the Markdown text to HTML and set the css of highlight.js to hit the code block.

```ts
import { marked } from 'marked';
import hljs from 'highlight.js';

const gfm_text = ""

marked.setOptions({
  highlight: function (code, lang) {
    const language = hljs.getLanguage(lang) ? lang : 'plaintext';
    return hljs.highlight(code, { language }).value;
  },
  langPrefix: 'hljs language-',
  gfm: true,
  breaks: true,
});

markd.parse(gfm_text)
```

### applying highlight.js css

style.scss

```scss
@import '~highlight.js/styles/github.css';
```

- - - 

This allows Markdown to be displayed in the same way as on GitHub. If the background- color of a code block is not present, please add css and apply it accordingly.

```scss
:host ::ng-deep pre > code {
  background-color: #f6f8fa;
  border-radius: 10px;
}
```

- - - 

tips: You can also override and customize the renderer in the following way

```ts
import { marked, Renderer } from 'marked';
import crypt from 'crypto-es';
import hljs from 'highlight.js';

const renderer = new Renderer();
/** ヘッダーにはテキストのhash値から生成したフラグメント, リンクをコピーするボタンを追加する */
renderer.heading = (text, lebel) => {
  const hash = crypt.MD5(text);
  return `
  <div class="d-flex">
    <h${lebel}
      id=${hash}
      style="border-left: solid 3px; border-color: darkturquoise; border-radius: 2px; padding-left: 5px;"
    >${text}</h${lebel}>
    <button class="btn btn-sm">
      <i class="bi bi-clipboard" onclick="window.navigator.clipboard.writeText('${window.location.origin}${window.location.pathname}#${hash}')"></i>
    </button>
  </div>
  `;
};
/** img要素にloading lazyを追加する */
renderer.image = (href) => `<img src=${href} loading=lazy />`;
/** リンク要素にbootstrap iconのリンクマークを付与する */
renderer.link = (href, title, text) =>
  `<a href=${href} class="text-muted">${text}<i class="bi bi-link-45deg"></i></a>`;
marked.setOptions({
  renderer,
  highlight: function (code, lang) {
    const language = hljs.getLanguage(lang) ? lang : 'plaintext';
    return hljs.highlight(code, { language }).value;
  },
  langPrefix: 'hljs language-',
  gfm: true,
  breaks: true,
});

```

This allowed us to render the GFM.

The actual source code used can be found [here](https://github.com/kemu3007/portal/blob/master/portal/src/app/shared/markdown/marked.service.ts).

- - - 

Revision history
-  crypto- js is a common js module and therefore migrated to the ECMAScript module crypto- es
